reviews.review_text: Keith-tastic If you like early Keith, boy oh boy will you like this show. He's really high in the mix for a good portion of the show and it's kind of cool to hear! He's certainly not Mr. Cosmic Jazz quite yet, but he's laying down some great rock n' roll keys. Well played throughout, very tight and Bakersfield-y.

Keith I can't stop listening to this show. The Keith-ness of it. Everyone sounds inspired and energized. The recording itself, sonically, reminds me of the Europe 72 recordings. I like that the Dark Star still has that menace they brought to it in '69 before it all got smoothed out later. Bill more than found his footing after Mickey's departure. The arrangements are just different enough from '72 arrangements to make them unique. More than a transitional show. And some hilarious banter and a weird nod to John Phillips Sousa to boot. Top notch show.
